Leaders accused of singing praises for Joho at night and the Kilifi governor during the day.Some lawmakers have endorsed Governor Joho for presidential contest. Malindi MP Aisha Jumwa says the bid for Coast unity may not succeed because some local leaders are double crossing Governors Amason Kingi (Kilifi) and his Mombasa colleague Hassan Joho. 

Ms Jumwa, who is Deputy President William Ruto’s regional pointperson, told Mr Kingi to tread carefully when dealing with local lawmakers “because they praise Joho at night and sing Kingi’s unity songs during the day”. 



