“I am a principled person who cannot be enticed with Sh20,000,” she said.  

The Malindi MP dismissed Mr Joho’s endorsement as the region’s spokesman, saying the governor does not have supporters beyond Mombasa.  

Mr Kingi told off leaders opposed to the call for Coast unity. 

“Coast has been known for squatters for decades. Being a  political squatter is a decision that must be dealt with now,” he said.  

clwanga@ke.nationmedia.com Supremacy fight has scuttled the long-touted formation of a Coast-based party ahead of Raila’s tour of region. Kingi told off politicians who are saying they won’t leave ODM. Struggling businesses, restless Kenyans deprived of night life waiting for the president’s address with bated breath. The leader was last seen in public late last month. Apart from three officials who were suspended, no one is yet to be charged in relation to the scandal.